REDFORD:
What is wrong with you, lady?

20:17.450 --> 20:18.518
KATE:
(growls)

20:24.491 --> 20:26.426
REDFORD:
This place is known as
the Deep Valley to the locals,

20:26.459 --> 20:28.595
they know it, you can leave your
bags and hire somebody

20:28.628 --> 20:30.797
to come get them.

20:30.830 --> 20:34.334
KATE:
Why don't you just let me ride
on the back of that thing,

20:34.367 --> 20:37.870
and then as soon as we get to
Snowy Pines I will hop off,

20:37.904 --> 20:39.406
I will pay you some money.

20:39.439 --> 20:40.940
REDFORD:
No, I don't want your money.

20:40.973 --> 20:42.609
KATE:
Okay, look, I'm sorry.

20:42.642 --> 20:45.278
I should not have
tried to follow you,

20:45.312 --> 20:49.616
but you can't blame a girl for
wanting to get to her wedding

20:49.649 --> 20:53.553
on time, and, and, and now
we're both here and we both

20:53.586 --> 20:56.055
need to get to
Snowy Pines, so--.

20:56.088 --> 20:57.757
REDFORD:
You know what, I have an idea.

20:57.790 --> 21:00.360
Why don't you just
push your wedding.

21:00.393 --> 21:01.561
KATE:
(laughing)

21:01.594 --> 21:03.963
You can't, you can't push a--
you can't push a wedding!

21:03.996 --> 21:07.033
There are guests coming in,
there's flowers that are

21:07.066 --> 21:09.669
supposed to be arriving today,
the venue's been booked

21:09.702 --> 21:11.070
for like a year,
where are you going,

21:11.103 --> 21:12.872
come on.

21:13.406 --> 21:14.341
(whimper)

21:15.207 --> 21:16.108
Will you please
please please please,

21:16.142 --> 21:18.411
will you please just
just take me on your

21:18.445 --> 21:20.313
snow thingy?

21:20.347 --> 21:22.649
You, come on,
you can't just leave me--.

21:22.682 --> 21:23.416
REDFORD: (shouts)
Come on!

21:23.450 --> 21:25.585
Really!?

21:28.455 --> 21:29.522
One bag.

21:29.556 --> 21:30.557
KATE:
One bag.

21:30.590 --> 21:31.424
REDFORD:
No more hitting.

21:31.458 --> 21:32.725
KATE:
No hitting.

21:32.759 --> 21:33.826
REDFORD:
And do us both a favour,
no more talking.

21:33.860 --> 21:36.429
KATE:
I, 'kay, I am mute.

21:36.463 --> 21:45.938
(***)

21:47.574 --> 21:48.941
EDWARD:
You're the one who insisted,

21:48.975 --> 21:50.943
at considerable
expense I might add,

21:50.977 --> 21:52.879
that the muffs be real fur.

21:52.912 --> 21:55.648
DIANE:
Yes well in your vast experience
in dealing with muffs, dear,

21:55.682 --> 21:57.917
don't you think it's best
to stick to the real thing?

21:57.950 --> 21:59.719
BRAD:
Uh, okay, so here's the latest.

21:59.752 --> 22:03.055
She's on her way here now,
and she's still

22:03.089 --> 22:05.358
riding a snowmobile
with a guy,

22:05.392 --> 22:07.126
but they'll be here in three
days and she says not to

22:07.159 --> 22:09.028
cancel anything.

22:09.061 --> 22:10.930
EDWARD:
Dear Lord.

22:10.963 --> 22:13.766
Do you have any idea
how this affects me?

22:13.800 --> 22:15.435
DIANE:
Yes dear.

22:15.468 --> 22:17.704
It's all about you.

22:17.737 --> 22:19.839
(kiss)

22:20.507 --> 22:21.608
DIANE:
What else?

22:21.641 --> 22:23.476
BRAD:
Just that she's sorry
she's not here yet,

22:23.510 --> 22:26.012
and she knows it's a
major inconvenience,

22:26.045 --> 22:28.548
for you especially.

22:29.949 --> 22:31.418
(***)

22:31.451 --> 22:33.152
BRAD:
Uh...just don't
cancel anything.

22:33.185 --> 22:35.488
She'll deal with whatever's
left when she gets back.

22:35.522 --> 22:36.689
DIANE:
Okay.

22:36.723 --> 22:39.892
I'll um, I'll deal with
the planner.

22:39.926 --> 22:43.095
(***)

22:43.129 --> 22:48.134
EDWARD:
Uh, Brad, why don't you go
to your future

22:48.167 --> 22:52.505
mother-in-law,
and comfort her.

22:54.073 --> 22:55.508
Cindy!

22:55.775 --> 22:56.609
(chair scrapes)

22:56.943 --> 23:02.615
(***)

23:02.815 --> 23:03.783
EDWARD:
(laughing)

23:03.816 --> 23:12.959
Uh, so...you....don't.

23:14.193 --> 23:15.828
CINDY:
Don't?

23:15.862 --> 23:17.396
EDWARD:
Don't.

23:18.164 --> 23:19.932
(engine revving)

23:19.966 --> 23:29.976
(***)

23:30.009 --> 23:40.019
(***)

23:40.052 --> 23:46.559
(***)

23:46.593 --> 23:48.828
(match strike)

23:52.031 --> 23:53.432
(lantern creaks)

23:59.739 --> 24:02.709
KATE:
Whose...whose place is this?

24:04.711 --> 24:06.479
REDFORD:
No idea.

24:06.513 --> 24:08.147
But it's shelter.

24:11.551 --> 24:14.521
Think you can
manage to start a fire?

24:14.754 --> 24:16.523
KATE:
Uh-huh, yep.

24:16.556 --> 24:18.024
REDFORD:
Alright, kindling's there.

24:18.057 --> 24:21.227
I'll go and get some more
firewood.

24:21.260 --> 24:23.229
KATE:
Okay.

24:23.963 --> 24:27.099
(door creaks)

24:27.133 --> 24:38.911
(***)

24:38.945 --> 24:40.012
(match strike)

24:47.053 --> 24:49.889
(match strike)

24:49.922 --> 24:59.932
(***)

24:59.966 --> 25:14.213
(***)

25:14.246 --> 25:15.815
KATE:
Hmm.

25:18.117 --> 25:19.619
(***)

25:19.652 --> 25:20.953
(lantern clacks)

25:22.622 --> 25:23.990
(thud)

25:24.023 --> 25:31.097
(***)

25:31.130 --> 25:34.734
(squirting)

25:36.769 --> 25:39.005
(squirting)

25:39.038 --> 25:41.173
KATE:
Oh, ugh.

25:42.174 --> 25:43.175
Hmm.

25:43.209 --> 25:47.914
(squirting)

25:47.947 --> 25:49.215
(air huffs
from empty bottle)

25:51.751 --> 25:54.086
KATE:
(sighs)

25:54.320 --> 25:55.888
(match strike)

25:55.922 --> 25:57.624
(loud bang)

25:57.857 --> 25:58.991
KATE:
Kate!

25:59.025 --> 26:00.259
Kate!

26:00.292 --> 26:11.604
(***)

26:11.638 --> 26:14.006
KATE:
(gasping)

26:14.040 --> 26:20.579
REDFORD:
(gasping)

26:22.915 --> 26:24.751
(match strike)

26:26.719 --> 26:28.187
KATE:
Still nothing.

26:33.425 --> 26:35.294
Still nothing.

26:50.877 --> 26:53.746
REDFORD:
Three things to make a fire.

26:53.780 --> 26:55.181
Fuel.

26:55.214 --> 26:56.716
Spark.

26:56.749 --> 26:58.317
Oxygen.

26:58.350 --> 27:00.286
That's it.

27:04.957 --> 27:08.060
For your face.

27:11.163 --> 27:14.200
I guess I'll
sleep on the floor.

27:15.201 --> 27:17.036
KATE:
Um, that's okay, I, I--.

27:17.069 --> 27:18.805
REDFORD:
No, I'll go get my sleeping bag.

27:18.838 --> 27:21.874
You just...take that.

27:24.210 --> 27:27.079
(door opens and shuts)

27:27.814 --> 27:37.824
(***)

27:37.857 --> 27:47.867
(***)

27:47.900 --> 28:01.480
(***)

28:01.513 --> 28:05.451
(door opens and shuts)

28:11.257 --> 28:13.359
REDFORD:
(huffs)

28:14.193 --> 28:19.966
(***)

28:19.999 --> 28:21.233
REDFORD:
(huffs)

28:21.267 --> 28:31.277
(***)

28:31.310 --> 28:41.320
(***)

28:41.353 --> 28:48.127
(***)

28:48.160 --> 28:49.161
REDFORD:
(sigh)

28:49.195 --> 28:50.863
Damn light.

28:50.897 --> 28:52.098
Son of a--.

28:52.131 --> 28:55.067
KATE:
No, you know what,
let me do it.

29:02.274 --> 29:05.011
Okay, how do I, uh...

29:05.044 --> 29:08.047
REDFORD:
Remove one of the necessary
elements.

29:12.084 --> 29:13.552
There you go.

29:13.585 --> 29:15.521
Congratulations.

29:24.063 --> 29:28.000
(rustling)

29:33.472 --> 29:35.174
KATE:
Redford?

29:36.475 --> 29:37.776
REDFORD:
What?

29:39.846 --> 29:40.913
KATE:
Thank you.

29:42.581 --> 29:43.816
REDFORD:
Goodnight.

29:46.252 --> 29:47.219
KATE:
Night.

29:52.892 --> 29:56.428
(owl hooting)

30:00.266 --> 30:08.340
(fire crackling)

30:08.374 --> 30:11.577
(sleeping bag rustling)

30:23.489 --> 30:25.858
(door creaks open and shut)

30:28.060 --> 30:29.561
(***)

30:29.595 --> 30:32.965
REDFORD:
(shivers)

30:35.334 --> 30:37.269
Ohh.

30:40.172 --> 30:41.974
Alright.

30:43.109 --> 30:44.476
(door creaks)

30:47.947 --> 30:51.017
REDFORD:
Ooh, that's cold.

30:53.019 --> 30:55.654
Ohh.

30:55.687 --> 30:57.556
(huffs)

30:57.589 --> 31:05.264
(***)

31:05.297 --> 31:11.603
(footsteps)

31:11.637 --> 31:13.973
(***)

31:14.006 --> 31:19.611
(creaking)

31:28.020 --> 31:31.590
(***)

31:31.623 --> 31:33.059
KATE:
Redford!

31:33.092 --> 31:34.193
Redford!

31:34.226 --> 31:36.128
REDFORD:
Lady, come on!

31:36.162 --> 31:38.497
You couldn't choose a
better time than this?

31:39.065 --> 31:40.232
Ugh!

31:40.266 --> 31:43.335
(door creaks)

31:45.137 --> 31:48.240
TRAPPER:
In or out, cowboy,
you're letting the cold in.

31:48.674 --> 31:52.979
Well, looks like
we got ourselves

31:53.012 --> 31:56.182
a menage a travoir here.

31:56.215 --> 31:59.986
This one here is
yours I suppose?

32:00.019 --> 32:02.354
What do you think
this heres pelt's worth?

32:02.388 --> 32:04.156
REDFORD:
I'm not in the fur business.

32:04.190 --> 32:06.292
TRAPPER:
Well, take a guess.

32:06.325 --> 32:08.327
REDFORD:
I don't speculate.

32:08.360 --> 32:10.429
TRAPPER:
My cabin, my rules, cowboy.

32:10.462 --> 32:13.199
What do you think this pale
quiver in the corner's worth,

32:13.232 --> 32:16.135
in the open market?

32:16.168 --> 32:17.970
REDFORD:
I'm guessing not much.

32:18.004 --> 32:20.539
TRAPPER:
(laughing)

32:20.572 --> 32:22.341
I'm guessing you're right.

32:22.374 --> 32:26.312
You can go, missy.

32:26.345 --> 32:28.014
KATE:
You--I--I can just go?

32:28.047 --> 32:30.082
TRAPPER:
Yeah, go,
get out of here,

32:30.116 --> 32:33.085
get on that machine of yours,
and get the hell out of here

32:33.119 --> 32:35.421
and off my trap line.

32:35.621 --> 32:36.488
REDFORD:
Come on, let's go.

32:36.522 --> 32:37.689
TRAPPER:
Ah-ah!

32:37.723 --> 32:40.359
Not you, cowboy.

32:40.392 --> 32:42.161
You stay put.

32:42.194 --> 32:44.396
KATE:
Oh, you've got to be
kidding me.

32:44.430 --> 32:45.297
(scoffs)

32:45.331 --> 32:48.167
TRAPPER:
Do I look
like I'm kidding?

32:49.268 --> 32:50.736
KATE:
Yeah, okay.

32:51.737 --> 32:52.638
Oh!

32:52.671 --> 32:54.706
I need the keys.

32:55.641 --> 32:57.276
TRAPPER:
Give her the keys.

32:57.676 --> 32:58.544
(keys jingle)

32:58.577 --> 32:59.678
KATE:
Thanks.

33:01.247 --> 33:03.749
(door opens and shuts)

33:04.683 --> 33:07.986
TRAPPER:
(laughing)

33:08.254 --> 33:10.489
(gargling)

33:10.722 --> 33:12.191
(spitting)

33:12.724 --> 33:13.759
It's harsh.

33:13.792 --> 33:15.994
(laughing)

33:16.728 --> 33:18.697
(snowmobile revving outside)

33:19.398 --> 33:21.033
TRAPPER:
Blrrr.

33:21.833 --> 33:23.502
Ah.

33:23.535 --> 33:25.404
I had a good day today.

33:25.437 --> 33:26.538
Really I did.

33:26.572 --> 33:30.476
But I didn't think it was
gonna turn out this good.

33:30.509 --> 33:33.745
Come on, you got
a pretty mouth.

33:33.779 --> 33:35.814
(laughing)

33:35.847 --> 33:38.784
It's just you and me.

33:38.817 --> 33:40.586
Really cold outside.

33:40.619 --> 33:42.054
Huh?

33:42.088 --> 33:44.223
We're far far away
from everything.

33:44.256 --> 33:45.757
(door clacks)

33:46.592 --> 33:49.261
TRAPPER:
God damn it lady
we had a deal!

33:49.295 --> 33:50.429
(thud)

33:50.462 --> 33:52.231
(crash)

33:52.798 --> 33:54.233
REDFORD:
Let's go, let's go!

33:55.101 --> 34:02.074
(engine idling)

34:02.108 --> 34:02.641
KATE:(mocking)
What's she worth to you?

34:02.674 --> 34:04.110
Oh, not much.

34:04.143 --> 34:05.043
REDFORD:
What are you upset about,

34:05.077 --> 34:06.445
it's not your hide
he was interested in!

34:06.478 --> 34:08.647
KATE:
Ah!

34:12.150 --> 34:13.719
TRAPPER:
Don't go, cowboy!

34:13.752 --> 34:17.556
I got the coonskins in
there if you wanna stay!

34:17.589 --> 34:18.389
Ugh!

34:18.424 --> 34:20.326
(thud)

34:20.792 --> 34:23.161
TRAPPER:
Fox pelts!

34:23.195 --> 34:26.232
Beaver!!

34:26.764 --> 34:28.500
Ugh.

34:28.534 --> 34:30.469
I'm so lonely.

34:31.203 --> 34:43.748
(birds chirping)

34:57.696 --> 35:04.536
(rustling)

35:12.244 --> 35:13.912
REDFORD:
I can't believe that
your heap of a fire

35:13.945 --> 35:15.647
is still burning.

35:15.681 --> 35:18.684
KATE:
Well I can't believe
you left my bags back there.

35:19.651 --> 35:21.887
The one thing we've learned
is to not leave me in charge

35:21.920 --> 35:24.390
of building fires.

35:24.656 --> 35:26.458
REDFORD:
Yeah.

35:26.492 --> 35:28.460
But that looks good on you.

35:28.494 --> 35:30.262
Better on you than me.

35:31.663 --> 35:32.564
KATE:
What a night.

35:32.598 --> 35:35.167
I'm starving.

35:35.934 --> 35:39.171
REDFORD:
There's some
beef jerky in that bag.

35:41.473 --> 35:43.209
KATE:
So?

35:43.242 --> 35:45.277
What's your story?

35:48.347 --> 35:50.216
REDFORD:
Wha...what story?

35:50.249 --> 35:51.450
KATE:
Well I mean you live
out in the middle of nowhere

35:51.483 --> 35:53.452
because...?

35:53.485 --> 35:55.287
REDFORD:
Because it suits me?

35:55.321 --> 35:56.788
KATE:
Okay, well what do you do?

35:56.822 --> 35:58.724
REDFORD:
About what?

35:58.757 --> 36:01.560
KATE:
For a living.

36:03.395 --> 36:04.763
REDFORD:
I don't ask pointless questions,

36:04.796 --> 36:05.797
how about that?

36:05.831 --> 36:06.898
KATE:
Ah, okay.

36:06.932 --> 36:10.336
Well in my experience
guys like you live out--gah,

36:10.369 --> 36:12.938
out in the middle of
nowhere for two reasons.

36:12.971 --> 36:16.308
One is money,
and the other is to be alone,

36:16.342 --> 36:18.477
so I'm guessing
a bit of both with you.

36:18.510 --> 36:23.849
Uh, are you a...oil rigger?

36:23.882 --> 36:26.485
Um, miner?

36:26.518 --> 36:29.388
Construction worker, mechanic?

36:29.421 --> 36:32.791
REDFORD:
No, and why don't you
just stop talking?

36:32.824 --> 36:36.228
KATE:
So we can take
Public Relations off the list?

36:36.262 --> 36:37.796
REDFORD:
(laughing)

36:38.364 --> 36:39.365
And what about you?

36:39.398 --> 36:40.532
KATE:
What about me?

36:40.566 --> 36:41.933
REDFORD:
What's a rich city girl doing
living out in

36:41.967 --> 36:43.669
Sorenson Lake?

36:43.702 --> 36:44.736
KATE:
What?

36:44.770 --> 36:47.473
REDFORD:
Well I mean
you got a $10,000 ring on.

36:47.506 --> 36:49.341
KATE:
Well I didn't buy it.

36:49.375 --> 36:51.510
REDFORD:
Okay, so he's
the rich one, yeah.

36:51.543 --> 36:54.346
KATE:
I teach out here
because I wanna

36:54.380 --> 36:56.715
make the community better.

36:56.748 --> 37:00.619
Helping people
is what matters to me.

37:02.621 --> 37:05.291
It's 15, by the way.

37:06.925 --> 37:08.627
REDFORD:
15 what?

37:08.660 --> 37:10.296
KATE:
The ring.

37:10.329 --> 37:12.564
You were
impressively close though.

37:12.598 --> 37:13.799
REDFORD:
They've gone up in price.

37:13.832 --> 37:16.902
KATE:
Oooh, well there's a
little crack in the armour.

37:16.935 --> 37:19.538
Stoic Redford
bought a diamond,

37:19.571 --> 37:22.341
but I'm guessing not for the
girl you're about to go see.

37:23.008 --> 37:24.943
What's her name?

37:24.976 --> 37:26.678
REDFORD:
Jodi.

37:26.712 --> 37:27.813
KATE:
Jodi.

37:27.846 --> 37:28.747
Hmm.

37:28.780 --> 37:31.783
Does she spell it
with an 'i' or a 'y'?

37:31.817 --> 37:33.785
REDFORD:
With an 'i'.

37:33.819 --> 37:36.254
KATE:
Does she dot her
'i' with a little heart?

37:36.555 --> 37:38.390
She work at Hooters?

37:41.092 --> 37:43.595
I'm sorry,
I'm not being nice.

37:43.629 --> 37:47.633
REDFORD:
It's fine, 'cause nice won't
get you across the river.

37:47.666 --> 37:49.668
KATE:
And being a jerk will?

37:49.701 --> 37:51.837
REDFORD:
I guess we'll see, won't we.

37:52.771 --> 37:55.374
KATE:
(sighs)

37:55.407 --> 38:00.712
(***)

38:00.746 --> 38:02.047
REDFORD:
You...you go
make yourself comfortable.

38:02.080 --> 38:03.549
KATE:
Okay.

38:03.582 --> 38:05.384
REDFORD:
I'll do all the hard work,
that's fine.

38:05.417 --> 38:06.752
KATE:
Okay, thanks.

38:06.785 --> 38:16.795
(***)

38:16.828 --> 38:27.105
(***)

38:27.138 --> 38:29.675
(engine revving)

38:29.708 --> 38:32.043
KATE:
Stop!

38:32.077 --> 38:33.412
REDFORD:
What, no, we got
ground to cover--.

38:33.445 --> 38:34.780
KATE:
I have to pee.

38:34.813 --> 38:36.515
REDFORD:
No, no, before dark,
if we don't make it--.

38:36.548 --> 38:37.816
KATE:
Okay, it's your jumpsuit,

38:37.849 --> 38:39.418
let's keep going then.

38:39.451 --> 38:40.619
REDFORD:
(sighs)

38:40.652 --> 38:42.120
KATE:
I'll be five minutes.

38:42.153 --> 38:43.455
Less.

38:43.489 --> 38:54.132
(***)

38:54.165 --> 38:57.369
KATE:
Ugh.

39:01.507 --> 39:03.875
KATE:
Redford!

39:03.909 --> 39:06.712
(***)

39:06.745 --> 39:08.614
(rustling)

39:08.980 --> 39:12.951
KATE:
My zipper's stuck,
can you help me?

39:12.984 --> 39:14.886
Come on, hurry.

39:14.920 --> 39:17.589
REDFORD:
Come on.

39:20.759 --> 39:21.760
Alright.

39:21.793 --> 39:23.094
KATE:
What are you-- oh, God.

39:23.128 --> 39:27.065
Just...

39:27.098 --> 39:29.668
REDFORD:
Okay.

39:29.701 --> 39:30.902
There.

39:30.936 --> 39:31.903
KATE:
Thanks.

39:31.937 --> 39:32.370
REDFORD:
Think you can
handle it from here?

39:32.404 --> 39:33.705
KATE:
Yeah.

39:33.739 --> 39:35.474
Okay, go away.

39:39.578 --> 39:41.913
Ugh, come on,
